Step 1: Create a new HDFS directory called CovidHDFS

Command:

hdfs dfs -mkdir /CovidHDFS
hdfs dfs -ls /

ğŸ‘‰ This creates a directory in HDFS to store your imported data.


---

Step 2: Import data from MySQL table CovidData into HDFS

Youâ€™ll use Sqoop import here.

Command:

sqoop import \
--connect jdbc:mysql://localhost/databasename \
--username root \
--password yourpassword \
--table CovidData \
--m 1 \
--target-dir /CovidHDFS

ğŸ§  Explanation:

--connect â†’ MySQL connection string

--table CovidData â†’ Your MySQL table

--m 1 â†’ Single mapper (as required)

--target-dir â†’ Destination HDFS folder


âœ… After import, check data:

hdfs dfs -ls /CovidHDFS


---

Step 3: Copy files from CovidHDFS to backup folder CovidData_Backup

Command:

hdfs dfs -cp /CovidHDFS /CovidData_Backup

Check it:

hdfs dfs -ls /CovidData_Backup


---

Step 4: Display first 1 KB of data

Command:

hdfs dfs -cat /CovidHDFS/part-m-00000 | head -c 1024

ğŸ“(Hint: â€œheadâ€ â†’ first bytes of file)


---

Step 5: Display last 1 KB of data

Command:

hdfs dfs -cat /CovidHDFS/part-m-00000 | tail -c 1024

ğŸ“(Hint: â€œtailâ€ â†’ last bytes of file)


---

Step 6: Transfer only Asia-related records

Here, youâ€™ll filter during Sqoop import using --where condition.

Command:

sqoop import \
--connect jdbc:mysql://localhost/databasename \
--username root \
--password yourpassword \
--table CovidData \
--m 1 \
--target-dir /SqoopCovid.AsiaData \
--where "continent='Asia'"

âœ… This imports only rows where the continent column = 'Asia'.


---

Step 7: Transfer only non-vaccinated people

Same logic â€” filter using --where again.

Command:

sqoop import \
--connect jdbc:mysql://localhost/databasename \
--username root \
--password yourpassword \
--table CovidData \
--m 1 \
--target-dir /SqoopNonVaccinated \
--where "vaccinated='No'"


---

âœ… Final HDFS Verification

hdfs dfs -ls /
hdfs dfs -cat /SqoopCovid.AsiaData/part-m-00000 | head
hdfs dfs -cat /SqoopNonVaccinated/part-m-00000 | head

